  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half and deseed&nbsp;(scrape the pith out with a teaspoon), then cut into thin strips&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Peel and&nbsp;slice the <strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;finely</p>\r\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/740.-step--1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/740.-step--1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/740.-step--1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/740.-step--1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/740.-step--1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>paneer</strong> into bite-size pieces&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid and a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> paneer</strong> and cook for 2-3 min, turning occasionally until golden, then transfer to a plate and set aside, reserving the pan</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/740.-step--2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/740.-step--2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/740.-step--2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/740.-step--2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/740.-step--2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium-high heat - if it's looking a little dry add a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>pepper</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>onion</strong> and a large pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 3 min, then reduce the heat to low and cook for 15 min or until softened and caramelised</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/740.-step--3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/740.-step--3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/740.-step--3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/740.-step--3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/740.-step--3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Meanwhile, place the <strong>coconut cream sachet[s]</strong> in a mug and cover with boiled water</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Peel the <strong>ginger</strong> (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and the<strong> garlic</strong>, then finely chop (or grate) both</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Bash the <strong>lemongrass</strong>, cut it down the middle lengthways, remove the tough outer leaves (keep for step 5) and chop the innards finely&nbsp;</span></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
